&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;TOBERMAN NEIGHBORHOOD CENTER&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Toberman Neighborhood Center (TNC) is a community non-profit organization with $3-5 million of annual expenses, 50-60 employees, and a large operating facility in the San Pedro Harbor area. TNC serves San Pedro, Wilmington, Harbor Gateway, Harbor City and Long Beach, providing family services including a variety of free programs to inspire change and enable the development of a better future. These services include: an after-school K-12 program, a gang intervention and prevention program, academic resources that address student achievement, safe supervised recreational activities, and educational courses including tutoring, study skills training, and instructions on secondary school completion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Toberman Neighborhood Center also promotes athletics and physical fitness for our youth through organized sports and recreational activities as well summer camps. Family Source Center (FSC) provides individual services and resources through pre-employment and employment support, housing, rental and utility assistance, GED, ESL, and after-school programming, computer literacy and financial literacy case management. In addition, TNC has a food pantry which provides groceries to individuals and families in need and a Thrift store for a wide variety of low-cost household items and clothing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE POSITION&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Executive Director (ED) serves as the strategic, operational, and community leader of Toberman Neighborhood Center (TNC). The ED is responsible for advancing TNC’s mission through collaborative community engagement, strong organizational leadership, sustainable fund development, operational excellence, and a healthy, people-centered organizational culture.&amp;nbsp;The Executive Director works collaboratively with the Board of Directors, staff, community partners, funders, and stakeholders to ensure TNC remains a trusted, responsive, and innovative community-based organization. The ED must demonstrate emotional intelligence, cultural humility, transparency, accountability, and a deep commitment to serving historically underserved communities.&amp;nbsp;The Executive Director will prioritize strengthening organizational infrastructure, staff development and retention, strategic planning, youth and family engagement, financial sustainability, trauma-informed leadership practices, and operational consistency while preserving TNC’s longstanding reputation and community trust.&lt;/p&gt;
