&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT PROSPERITY NOW&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Prosperity Now, we help communities and organizations strengthen financial security through practical tools, research, and partnerships. Our approach is to innovate, incubate, activate, and elevate new and existing systems-oriented solutions that address the root causes of economic barriers to opportunity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THE POSITION&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Finance and Accounting Manager is responsible for managing the day-to-day accounting and financial operations of Prosperity Now and ensuring the accuracy, integrity, and timeliness of the organization’s financial records and reporting. Working closely with the Chief Financial Officer (CFO), Finance staff, and cross-functional teams, this hands-on role oversees the month-end and year-end close processes, general ledger, accounts payable, accounts receivable, account reconciliations, and compliance with applicable accounting standards, grant and contract requirements, and organizational policies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the CFO, the Finance and Accounting Manager serves as a key financial partner to Finance, Business Development, and Program staff, supporting budgeting, forecasting, grant and contract financial management, and internal and external financial reporting. The role provides oversight of restricted grant accounting, cost allocations, financial compliance, and the development and maintenance of strong internal controls. The Finance and Accounting Manager also plays an important role in strengthening the organization’s financial infrastructure by improving accounting processes, increasing efficiency, and ensuring that financial information is accurate, accessible, and useful for decision-making. The successful candidate will combine strong technical accounting expertise with a collaborative and service-oriented approach and the ability to translate financial requirements into practical guidance for colleagues across the organization.&lt;/p&gt;
